Following is notice "Hi Kristin, I found out yesterday that an Afghan refugee mother delivered a baby here in Maine 5 weeks ago.  I cannot find delivery in hospital. Her name is Medina Fahimi, DOB 4/4/1996 and babyÃ????Ã???Ã??Ã?Â¢??s name is Aryan Fahimi, DOB 1/3/2022, male. Father is HMad Hakimi, DOB 11/7/1989. Per Dr. William Frank at the Immigration Clinic in Saco, the baby had first HBV and HBIG within 24 hours.  Baby will be seen by Dr. Maura Price, 294-5959  but I am not sure if he has had his 1-2 month HBV yet? The family speaks Pashto language. Dr. William Frank is retired and hard to reach. He is treating the family except for their three kids who will be seen by Dr. Price. His number is 207-459-0672.  Let me know if you need anything else.  I do not yet have confirmation of mom's HBsAg but her children born in Afghanistan are HbsAg positive. Megan" 3/10 Call from Dr. Frank regarding this case and family. He was following up on the whole family to make sure he reported cases. Thanked him for diligence. Children (Saana, Usman, Aryan) see Maura Price and Peds GI at Maine Med, mom (this case) sees Jodi Ryan, dad (Hmad) sees Dr. Frank.  No sx and no LFT's drawn. Jody was ordering HBV confirmation to follow up on previous marker. Discussed HAV vaccine again with all providers. -- New HBV+ labs >6 months from first. Updated to Confirmed. HS 12/27/22

Investigation General Comments: 3/15 Call from ED at LincolnHealth reporting case. Case seen at LH ED on 3/14 for nausea vomiting and jaundice. Was HAV and HCV negative 9 months ago. Now presenting with HAV, HBV, HCV co-infection and escalating liver enzymes. Case wanted to leave AMA but was encouraged to stay to monitor for fulminant live failure and encephalopathy. Transferred to PBMC and put on Brigham and Women's Hospital transplant list as precaution. Has IVDU history and has used IVD in last 4 months. Spoke with friend and girlfriend who have had close contact and possible IVDU sharing. Arranged HAV (although they are outside 2 week window for first contact while he was infectious) and HBV vaccine as needed (gf has this) They will also get hepatitis and CMP testing done. They are not symptomatic currently.

Given elevated ALT is not new, considering chronic.
